ABUJA (SundiataPost) – After what looked like flattening the curve for two days, Lagos on Monday resumed spike in new cases of COVID-19 as Nigeria’s number of confirmed cases move towards 13,000.According to update released by the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control (NCDC) late on Monday night, Lagos resumed lead in new infections with 128 new confirmed cases out of the 315 new infections  reported by the NCDC. This brings the total number of confirmed COVID-19 infections in Nigeria to 12,801.For two days previously namely Saturday and Sunday, the rate of new infections in Lagos had lowered raising excitement that Lagos had reached its peak and there was going to be reduction in infections henceforth. The full report is as follows: 315 new cases of #COVID19; Lagos- 128FCT-34Rivers- 32Edo- 28Oyo- 22Kaduna- 20Gombe- 13Ogun- 8Plateau- 5Delta- 7Kwara- 7Kano- 5Bauchi- 4Katsina- 2 12801 cases of #COVID19NigeriaDischarged: 4040Deaths: 361 See the State by state breakdown below ABUJA - For the first time since the outbreak of the coronavirus pandemic in Nigeria, Kano has recorded the highest infection in a single day as reported by the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control (NCDC) on Monday night. Kano had 23 new confirmed cases on Monday. In Lagos, which has… April 21, 2020 In "Top Stories" As Nigeria recorded its 97th COVID-19 case late on Saturday, a review of official data shows that the number of confirmed cases rose by 340 per cent in a week. COVID-19 is a deadly respiratory disease caused by the coronavirus. According to the latest breakdown by the Nigeria Centre for… March 29, 2020 In "News" ABUJA (SundiataPost) - Nigeria's COVID-19 infections continue to increase at an alarming rate, according to update released by the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control (NCDC) on Saturday night.Nigeria now has 12,233 confirmed cases.However, one important development is that the number of infections in Lagos reduced while there seems to be… June 7, 2020 In "Top Stories"